The principal characters in the story are Sherlock Holmes, Dr. John Watson, and Sir Henry Baskerville. Holmes is a brilliant detective with unparalleled deductive skills. Dr. Watson is his loyal friend and the narrator of the story. Sir Henry Baskerville is the last heir of the Baskerville family, and he seeks Holmes' assistance in unraveling the mystery of the hound. Other notable characters include Dr. Mortimer, a family friend, and the enigmatic Barrymore family who live on the moor.
